DOC.brief_summary: The aim of the study is to investigate the ovulation inhibition of two 4-phasic oral contraceptive regimens.
DOC.brief_title: Ovulation Inhibition of Two 4-phasic Oral Contraceptive Regimens
DOC.criteria: Healthy women willing to use nonhormonal methods of contraception Women with any contraindication for oral contraceptive use, for example but not limited to: presence or history of venous or arterial thrombotic / thrombembolic events, hypertension, presence or history of severe hepatic disease
